                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3169a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-14T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1919, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed July 11<note n="39" xml:id="d398fn39">Memorandum of the Third
                        Assistant Secretary of State of a conversation with the Japanese Chargé
                        (File No. 893.00/3165½); not printed.</note> by Japanese Embassy that
                    careful instructions had been cabled to Japanese Minister to consult you frankly
                    and fully and to co-operate with you in an effort to straighten out the
                    difficulty at Tientsin.</p>
                <p>You will please be guided by Department’s recent cable in the same matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
